.         ** Express the average gap as share of the (average) MEB
.         sum MEB if Gap_ref == 1 

{txt}    Variable {c |}        Obs        Mean    Std. dev.       Min        Max
{hline 13}{c +}{hline 57}
{space 9}MEB {c |}{res}        497    20082.95    1182.074      16968      21816
{txt}
{com}.         // calculate the average MEB for the reference cohort 
. /* reminder: in this example the MEB is differentiated by groups of household 
> size - if this is not the case this passage is not needed)      */
. 
.         gen PCGap_share_MEB = PCGap_avg / `r(mean)' if Gap_ref == 1
{txt}(518 missing values generated)

{com}.         // use the average MEB calculated in the previous line. 
.         // Note: this variable is defined only for the cohort
.         
.         label var PCGap_share_MEB "Gap/MEB per capita (cohort: below MEB and food insecure)"
{txt}
{com}. 
. *------------------------------------------------------------------------------*
. *  Estimate the gap by household size
. *------------------------------------------------------------------------------*
. 
. /* In this dataset different MEB values are provided for 4 categories of household
> size, to take into account household economies of scale: small (1-3), medium(4-6),
> large(7-9), extra-large (10+). Accordingly, different gaps will be estimated */
. 
.         ** Create a variable representing the different categories of household size
.         recode hhsize (1/3 = 1) (4/6 = 2) (7/9 = 3) (nonmissing = 4), gen(hhsize_cat)
{txt}(1,010 differences between {bf:hhsize} and {bf:hhsize_cat})

{com}.          
.         label var hhsize_cat    "Classes of household size"
{txt}
{com}.         label def hhsize                1 "Small" 2 "Medium" 3 "Large" 4 "Extra large"
{txt}
{com}.         label val hhsize_cat hhsize
{txt}
{com}.         order hhsize_cat, after(hhsize)
{txt}
{com}. 
.         ** Create a variable taking the average gap value for each household size category
.         gen PCGap_avg_hhcat = .
{txt}(1,015 missing values generated)

{com}.         label var PCGap_avg_hhcat "Average per capita gap per hh size (cohort: below MEB and food insecure)"
{txt}
{com}. 
.         ** Compute the average gap for household size cat and save into the variable created before
.         forvalues i = 1/4 {c -(} 
{txt}  2{com}.         // we will loop through the four household size categories
.         sum  PCGap if Gap_ref == 1  & hhsize_cat == `i' 
{txt}  3{com}.         // compute average for hh size cat within the gap analysis cohort
.         replace PCGap_avg_hhcat = `r(mean)' if Gap_ref == 1 & hhsize_cat == `i' 
{txt}  4{com}.         // store average into variable
.         {c )-}

{txt}    Variable {c |}        Obs        Mean    Std. dev.       Min        Max
{hline 13}{c +}{hline 57}
